As-Built (Current State) - BubbleBoard Web Hosting

# Overview (Current Implementation)

Currently in this stage, BubbleBoard has established the web hosting environment using AWS infrastructure. The public website endpoint has been deployed, reachable via the purchased domain using Amazon Route 53. The website currently displays a default index.html file that is stored in an Amazon S3 bucket configured for static website hosting

# Implemented Components

## Domain Acquired

Registered domain via Route 53 (bubbleboard.click)

## Static Hosting

S3 bucket created for static site hosting

Static website hosting enabled

Public read confiurged through bucket policy

## DNS Mapping

Route 53 hosted zone created automatically upon domain registration

Alias/A record created to map the domain to the S3 website endpoint

## Deployment Validation

Navigating to the custom domain resolves successfully

The default page loads as intended

## Architecture (For now)

It's still single tier at this stage

User -> Route S3 (DNS) -> S3 Static Website Hosting

## Infrastructure Details

| **Layer** | **Current Choice** |
